- We will think of coding as a conversation but with notations. Notations are a specialized vocabulary or system of symbols for communication. an example would be using "3g" instead of "Three grams" in cooking. The notations we will use is the programming language's rules or "syntax".
- Definition of "Programming": The act of creating programs: documents written in a notation system that can be understood by other humans as well as computers.
- Definition of "Programming Language": A programming language defines the rules of notation ("syntax") that are required for it to ask the computer to do work on your behalf.
